<p><span><span><span><span><span><span>14, Prokinetics are medications which help improve the functioning of the gastrointestinal tract. They are usually used to treat various gastrointestinal disorders such as GERD, gastroparesis, and functional dyspepsia. Prokinetics act on various receptors in the GI tract to improve motility and reduce acid reflux. Common prokinetic medications include Domperidone, Metoclopramide, Cisapride, and Erythromycin. They work by stimulating the peristaltic reflex, blocking serotonin receptors, and increasing acetylcholine release. Diphenoxylate is a synthetic opiod drug.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
