Axillary and pubic hair growth is not estrogen dependent because they are brought about by androgens, such as testosterone, instead of estrogen. Testosterone is responsible for the development of secondary sex characteristics, such as facial hair, body hair, and changes in muscle mass. Thus, axillary and pubic hair growth can occur even when estrogen levels are low. Cervical mucus is produced by the cervix when the hormone estrogen rises.<br />
